Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of swaps needed to have all couples sitting side by side. We can solve this problem by iterating through the array once and checking if the adjacent elements are not the correct couple. If they are not, we decrement the result by 2 (one for the swapped couple and another for the swapped seats).

The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the array once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the result variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few operations and does not require any significant energy consumption.

